@Styromaniac: well if you use the tor only mode then you address can't be found. 

It meets the strict definition of a darknet because it requires special software to access. It is also a darkweb because it hosts web content. 

I know it is possible to make clearnet access with the clearnet proxy,  however sofar it's been unsuccessful since it requires a lot of bandwidth and storage, as well as hosts some illegal content.
